Al/SiN/p-Si/Al device is analyzed by conductance-voltage characteristic with interface traps

Next, electrical measurements are carried out on the PERC cell device in both light and dark conditions. The device bias is applied to the Al bottom electrode, while the top electrode is ground. The sweeping range of the voltage is from − 1 to 0.75 V. Figure 6 shows the I-V characteristic under dark conditions. The current leakage is reduced significantly after HDH treatment, with the ratio of the decrease being about 0.5 orders. In addition, on the right side of the I-V characteristic, the hump of the on current is found to be reduced after the treatment. We also extract the I-V curve and convert it as the ideal factor following the diode current equation:
